                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>This TSI applies to 1000, 2000, 3000, 4000, and 8000 Series vehicles built after March 15, 1992
                    (approx.) with New General Instrument Cluster.
                </para>
                <para>Ammeters installed in International vehicles require the use of an external shunt. In a shunt
                    circuit, 98.9 to 99.1% of the current flows through the shunt with the balance through the ammeter.
                    Ammeter accuracy relies on the proper percentage of current flowing through both the shunt and
                    ammeter cables. In order to achieve this accuracy, the
                    <emph type="underscr">gauge and length</emph>
                    of the shunt and ammeter cables must be precisely determined.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <para>Below are listed some pre-calculated gauge and shunt wire lengths which can be used for field
                installation of ammeters (
                <hotlnk xrefid="t9208101">Table 1</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <table id="t9208101" frame="all">
                <title>Gauge and Shunt Wire Lengths</title>
                <tgroup cols="2" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="2.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="2.75in"/>
                    <spanspec namest="col1" nameend="col2" spanname="1to2"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="2" spanname="1to2" valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">150 Amp Ammeter (1690290C1)</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>Shunt Wire Length (4 gauge)</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>Ammeter Wire Length (16 gauge)*</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>4 ft. 1 inch</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>8 feet</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>4 ft. 4-1/4 inches</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>10 feet</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>4 ft. 7-3/4 inches</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>12 feet</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>4 ft. 11 inches</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>14 feet</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="2" spanname="1to2" valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">100 Amp Ammeter (1690291C1)</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>Shunt Wire Length (6 gauge)</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>Ammeter Wire Length (16 gauge)*</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>4 ft 7-1/2 inches</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>8 feet</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>4 ft. 11-1/4 inches</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>10 feet</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>5 ft. 3 inches</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>12 feet</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>5 ft. 6-3/4 inches</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>14 feet</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="2" spanname="1to2" valign="top">
                                <para>*Ammeter wire length is total of both cables to the ammeter. Both sides do not
                                    have to be equal length, but total must equal ammeter wire length.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para>
                <hotlnk xrefid="f9208101">Figure 1</hotlnk>
                shows a typical installation. Install ammeter in lower left hand corner of cluster. Connect the positive
                (+) ammeter cable to pin 7 of the yellow instrument harness connector. Connect the negative (-) ammeter
                cable to pin 16 of the yellow instrument harness connector. The part number of the terminal to use at
                both pins 7 and 16 is 1661598C1.
            </para>
            <figure id="f9208101" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9208101.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Ammeter Installation</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </tsi>
